basics.name: Anna Baker
basics.label: UI/UX Developer
basics.summary: Results-driven UX Developer with a strong background in front end development, passionate about creating intuitive and engaging user experiences. With [number] years of industry experience, I have a proven track record of collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver responsive web interfaces using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and various frameworks. Skilled in translating design mockups and wireframes into pixel-perfect, cross-browser-compatible web pages, I ensure seamless integration of design and functionality. Adept at conducting user research, usability testing, and leveraging data-driven insights to enhance the user experience. Proficient in version control systems, accessibility standards (WCAG), and design tools such as Figma and Adobe XD. I am eager to apply my skills and creativity to drive impactful user experiences and contribute to the success of your team.

position.title: adjunct faculty
summary: Developed and implemented powerful and compelling curricula for Type and Publication students, incorporating best practices, new and emerging trends, and software innovations.
Fostered an open and interactive classroom environment, encouraging student engagement, discussion, and collaborative learning.
Collaborated with other members of the university to develop and execute real-world projects, providing students with hands-on experience and elevating their portfolios.
Lectured on the intricacies of InDesign, typography, and layout grids, delivering engaging and informative lessons that enhanced students' understanding and mastery of these subjects.

position.title: UI/UX developer
summary: Developed and implemented responsive web interfaces using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, and .NET.
Collaborated closely with UI/UX designers and back-end developers to ensure seamless integration of design and functionality.
Translated design mockups and wireframes into pixel-perfect and cross-browser-compatible web pages.
Used version control systems such as Git to manage and collaborate on code repositories.
Implemented accessibility standards (WCAG) to ensure an inclusive and user-friendly experience for all users.

position.title: UI/UX designer
summary: Conducted user research and usability testing to gather insights and feedback, leveraging data-driven design decisions to enhance the user experience.
Developed and presented wireframes and interactive prototypes to communicate design concepts and interactions to stakeholders and development teams.
Collaborated closely with cross-functional teams including product managers, developers, and graphic designers to ensure seamless integration of design and functionality.
Contributed to the development and maintenance of design systems and style guides to ensure consistency across products and platforms.

position.title: web designer
summary: Collaborated with clients and stakeholders to understand project requirements, target audience, and brand guidelines.
Created wireframes and mockups to present design concepts, incorporating feedback to refine and finalize website designs.
Worked closely with developers to ensure seamless integration of design and functionality.
Utilized best practices in user experience design to enhance website usability and navigation.

position.title: layout designer
summary: Designed and created visually appealing layouts for print and digital materials including magazines, brochures, reports, and white papers using Adobe InDesign.
Collaborated with editors, writers, photographers, and other creative professionals to develop content that met the project objectives and audience needs.
Maintained brand standards and style guidelines, ensuring that all layouts were consistent with the brand identity and communicated the brand message effectively.

position.title: art director
summary: Led creative freelance teams in the development and execution of visual concepts for magazines, advertising campaigns, branding initiatives, and other marketing projects.
Managed 10+ brands and developed brand guidelines and design systems for each.
Created the layout and conducted pre-flight checks for 3 monthly magazines - each 52+ pages - delivering print-ready files to the printer in time for publication.
Managed timelines with project management software, ensuring that projects were delivered on time.
Assisted additional teams and magazines in the design and execution of their projects and magazines.

position.title: graphic designer and junior developer
summary: Designed, developed, and maintained web applications using PHP, MySQL, HTML, & CSS.
Produced print-ready files and digital assets, adhering to industry standards and client specifications.
Conceptualized and executed creative solutions that met client requirements, target audience needs, and brand standards.
Developed and maintained brand guidelines and design templates to ensure consistency across all visual materials.
Communicated with team members and stakeholders to understand project requirements, timelines, and budgets and to provide technical expertise.

position.title: freelance graphic designer
summary: Designed and produced visual materials including marketing collateral, user manuals, brochures, trade show materials, and website content using Adobe Suite and QuarkXPress.
Conceptualized and executed creative solutions that met client requirements, target audience needs, and brand standards.
